			>
			<P><EM>Competition is not the entire reason. Vansalior's post identifies the others.</EM> </P>
<P>Where is this post that you are referring to?&nbsp; I'm curious as to what the reasons are that he lists for PvP being fun.&nbsp; Could you be so kind as to post them here?</P>
<P><EM>What was your strategy on Discord?</EM></P>
<P>Discord had a final ending point - a way to "win".&nbsp; "Winning" on a normal server only means you succeed in driving off your competition until the server becomes boring and devoid of competition.&nbsp; Permanent servers have minor victories and losses daily - that is what makes them have longevity, and this is also why balance is so important for a long-term server.&nbsp; This again brings me back to the point as to why the server rule-set I outline would create a fun PvP environment.</P>
<P>If you disagree with the conclusions I make, state why my reasoning is incorrect and list support.&nbsp; </P>
<P>&nbsp;</P>
