			<a href='/eq/view_profile?user.id=26710'>







</a><br>
			


			
			<p>
			






<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=PVP&message.id=342#M342">12</a> of 127
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 2160 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV></DIV>
<DIV></DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I hope the devs will at least take a look at this thread.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Some specific things I agree/disagree with:</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I agree with the hardcoded two teams structure. This is essential to server longetivity, </DIV>
<DIV>and has been proven time and time again as what works best. I also wouldn't mind a FFA </DIV>
<DIV>server personally, where it's completely up to the players.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>XP loss on death, definitely. I liked permadeath the best to be honest.... but that </DIV>
<DIV>obviously isn't for everyone and would cause server population issues down the road. It </DIV>
<DIV>sure made PvP more intense though.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Expansions cap - old world and Kunark on release. Velious eventually, and nothing after </DIV>
<DIV>that. No AA points, no horses, etc.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I'm kind of divided on the item loot issue. Item loot is a great incenitive for PvP, but </DIV>
<DIV>there has to be some kind of balance put in place for melee classes. Or you'll see naked </DIV>
<DIV>casters ganking lower level melees all day.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I agree with putting a points system into play. I liked the one they had on Discord quite a </DIV>
<DIV>bit. In effect, players 20+ levels under you give zero points, and the closer players are </DIV>
<DIV>to your level, the more points you recieve. The best thing about this system was that it </DIV>
<DIV>even worked in groups. For example, me and a Necro were grouped and downed a higher level </DIV>
<DIV>Druid.... 16 points for both of us. I'm not sure how the Sullon Zek point system operates, </DIV>
<DIV>but I assume it's similar.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Item rewards for points would be a perfect incentive for PvP. Speaking of which, where is </DIV>
<DIV>my Discord item?</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>One character per account is vital. When you have mules, twinks, or level 1 trainers </DIV>
<DIV>running around, it just stinks up the place.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>An increase in debuff effectiveness would surely help Enchanters in PvP, but I worry about </DIV>
<DIV>how good some other classes might be with that, namely Bards and Shamans (malo). Class </DIV>
<DIV>Balance is incredibly important. As Trynd mentioned, the closest to relative "class </DIV>
<DIV>balance" on PvP servers was during the Kunark era. Old world had certain casters </DIV>
<DIV>overpowered at the high-end, and Velious introduced a noticeable gear gap between melees. </DIV>
<DIV>This is something that would need to be properly tuned or adjusted.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I agree with the reduction on nukes.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Faction hits in towns was always a good idea. It gave towns a more realistic, "safe zone" </DIV>
<DIV>feel to them, but didn't restrict PvP from taking place. It also made a lot more sense for </DIV>
<DIV>guards to attack someone killing one of their own guys. This would be even more effective </DIV>
<DIV>if the server was divided between two teams.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>A few things I'll add:</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Line-of-sight issues. The ideal setup would be spells AND songs requiring LoS to begin </DIV>
<DIV>casting in PvP. This would help melees out a little bit, and prevent casting through walls</DIV>
<DIV>/floors/etc.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Exp bonuses. An advanced exp rate for this server wouldn't be a bad idea. The actual rate </DIV>
<DIV>increase would depend on how much exp is lost for PvE/PvP deaths (ie: you lose a level for </DIV>
<DIV>PvP/PvE death, but gain exp 1.5x as fast).</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>And that's about all I can think of right now. The ideal setup for PvP would be very </DIV>
<DIV>similar to the PvP-teams servers, circa Ruins of Kunark.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>If other posters could offer constructive critcism or voice their support for the idea, </DIV>
<DIV>that would be nice. This is not a "let's make our dream server" type of thing. I've been </DIV>
<DIV>playing EQ since release, and on PvP servers for the vast majority of those years - as has </DIV>
<DIV>Trynd. This is simply what would work best, based on 5 years of observation and personal </DIV>
<DIV>experience.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>As for strategy on Discord, that was a unique server to say the least. Trind killed a </DIV>
<DIV>massive amount of low-level players without ever dying. I got about half my points that way </DIV>
<DIV>as well, and the other half came from a few solo high-end kills. Various "alliances" were </DIV>
<DIV>formed out of necessity (Darkenbane being there and all), with most of them breaking up </DIV>
<DIV>eventually.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Searyx the Executioner || Tallon Zek</DIV>	
		</td></tr>
