			<p>
			






<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=PVP&message.id=344#M344">13</a> of 127
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 2137 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<P>I tend to regard any ruleset that features item loot as a recipe for a short-term server.&nbsp; The difference in gear dependency between a warrior and say, a necro, is huge.&nbsp; Giving a warrior a bandaid fix by allowing him to protect 2-4 of his items is hardly going to cover that gap.&nbsp; Personally I favor lost experience as the penalty for losing, rather than item loss.&nbsp; Reward the winner via a point-based system; allow them to turn in points for reward items of their choice.</P>
<P>As a general rule, if risk is much greater than reward, the "logical" solution is to never PvP.&nbsp; Obviously some will do it anyway for sport.&nbsp; However item loot, particularly for melees, will serve to discourage people from coming to the server, and discourage those who do play from ever bothering to fight each other.&nbsp; To me the biggest issue facing PvP servers is that there is no reason to PvP in terms of advancement.&nbsp; So you see cross-team alliances for PvE.&nbsp; PvE always provides a route to advancement.</P>	
		</td></tr>
		<tr>
		
		<td class="msg_date_cell" valign=bottom nowrap>
		<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
		 <span class=date_text>04-20-2004</span> <span class=time_text>07:09 AM</span>
		</span>
		</td>

		
			<td colspan=2 class="msg_rating_cell" valign=bottom nowrap 
			
			>
			
				&nbsp;
				
				<br><br><a href="javascript:lipopup('/eq/notification?board.id=PVP&message.id=344&notification.type=1', 'notification', 600, 460, 'yes', 'yes')" class=text_smallest><u>Report Abuse to a Moderator</u></a>
				
		</td>
			
		</tr>
	</table>
	
		











	







