			<p>
			






<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=PVP&message.id=345#M345">14</a> of 127
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 2122 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<P>Well, the number of items that could be "protected" could be tweaked.&nbsp; Since casters have an inherent advantage in an item loot environment, it may be entirely reasonable to give melee's additional slots to protect, while still limiting casters to 2-4 items.&nbsp; Fortunately, this is a number that I imagine could be tweaked and refined based on game play and is not a major structural problem such as those introduced in post-Velious expansions.</P>
<P>I really want to highlight something Searyx said:</P>
<DIV><EM>If other posters could offer constructive critcism or voice their support for the idea, </EM></DIV>
<DIV><EM>that would be nice. This is not a "let's make our dream server" type of thing. I've been </EM></DIV>
<DIV><EM>playing EQ since release, and on PvP servers for the vast majority of those years - as has </EM></DIV>
<DIV><EM>Trynd. This is simply what would work best, based on 5 years of observation and personal </EM></DIV>
<DIV><EM>experience.</EM></DIV>
<DIV><EM></EM>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>This is absolutely my intent here.&nbsp; I love EQ pvp and want to help make it work.&nbsp; Creating a discussion that addresses the merits and weaknesses of this type of server would be the most constructive way to help get to a server rule-set that would indeed satisfy the demands of the customers (us).&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Xefin - Item loot also creates a reward for PvPing, not just a penalty.&nbsp; One possible solution is to allow people to turn in their "pvp points" that they earn for gear - especially melee gear / resist gear.&nbsp; Balance is still possible because when notorious pvpers get killed, they lose an item and therefore become easier to kill the next time.&nbsp; This encourages teamwork, while adding a large risk to solo PvP (but still encourages it, due to the lure of item loot).</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I really think that people would love this server, but I agree that the "protected status" of items may need balancing to ensure that melees have a chance - my main characters have always been melees by the way.&nbsp; <img src='/i/smilies/16x16_smiley-happy.gif' width=16 height=16 border=0></DIV>	
		</td></tr>
		<tr>
		
		<td class="msg_date_cell" valign=bottom nowrap>
		<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
		 <span class=date_text>04-20-2004</span> <span class=time_text>07:22 AM</span>
		</span>
		</td>

		
