		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			Item loot encourages bottom feeding and ganking.  If there is a reward for killing people who have no chance in defeating you people will do it, to the exclusion of getting into a fight where they might lose.  By the same token unless there is a definite loss from a PvP death there can be no reasonable reward for killing someone in PvP.  XP loss isn't really a problem when you have a 96% rez available which any sort of long-term server will have, so giving people the ability to "buy" items with kills won't work; you'll just have people trading off killing each other then getting a rez until everyone can get whatever they want.  That's why I don't think item loot or item rewards for PvP will work.
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
							Menre Nar'tredok<br>Arch Mage of the Crimson Praetorian<br>Blood and Honor!
