			<a href='/eq/view_profile?user.id=24860'>







</a><br>
			


			
			<p>
			






<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=PVP&message.id=350#M350">17</a> of 127
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 2104 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<EM>Item loot encourages bottom feeding and ganking. If there is a reward for killing people who have no chance in defeating you people will do it, to the exclusion of getting into a fight where they might lose. By the same token unless there is a definite loss from a PvP death there can be no reasonable reward for killing someone in PvP. XP loss isn't really a problem when you have a 96% rez available which any sort of long-term server will have, so giving people the ability to "buy" items with kills won't work; you'll just have people trading off killing each other then getting a rez until everyone can get whatever they want. That's why I don't think item loot or item rewards for PvP will work.</EM> 
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Killing the same person repeatedly will actually decrease your point total - the timeframe where this occurs can be tweaked.&nbsp; People kept saying Discord sucked because you could make a level one frog in Grobb, run him to Guk and kill him to gain points over and over - an obvious exploit.&nbsp; This problem was greatly overstated, I think the Darkenbane crew killed&nbsp;the&nbsp;handful of&nbsp;people who tried to do this and the problem was solved - I didn't even worry about it, I just killed everyone I could.&nbsp; The fear that people will exploit a point reward system to gain relatively minor items (resist gear, potions, whatever) is similiarly overstated if the ruleset is properly developed to make this difficult.&nbsp; Not only should the points necessary for rewards not be cheap, but if you kill the same person three times and then start losing points (say you need to wait 3 hours or something to gain positive points from them again) then this would be too much of a hassle to be worth it.&nbsp; It would be far more efficient to go kill real enemies.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>As far as item loot encouraging ganking - that is actually the point.&nbsp; Ganking means that players who play on this server will be afraid.&nbsp; They'll always be looking over their shoulder, they'll travel in groups, and they'll be loyal to their friends.&nbsp; Kill or be killed - this is what creates the fun pvp dynamic - this is the same reason that Discord was so much fun and was so intense.&nbsp; The penalty for death was massive!</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Plus, in the long term, resist gear will become available, and there will develop a relative equilibrium in the circulation of gear.&nbsp; Word will get out when some people start getting some uber gear and gank squads will form to go kill them.&nbsp; How is that not awesome?&nbsp; This keeps everyone on their toes!&nbsp; This would be the essence of what makes pvp fun!</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>	
		</td></tr>
		<tr>
		
		<td class="msg_date_cell" valign=bottom nowrap>
		<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
		 <span class=date_text>04-20-2004</span> <span class=time_text>09:13 AM</span>
		</span>
		</td>

		
