		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV>If its hardcoded two equal teams with a forced population balance cap, then there will be a built in equalizing force to naturally oppose the uber guild that takes the early lead.</FONT></DIV>
<DIV></FONT>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Alternatively, remove the Velious expansion and make it Kunark only.&nbsp; PvE gains from Kunark gear are not large enough to give characters an overwhelming PvP advantage (I personally don't think Velious gear is either - especially with item loot).</FONT></DIV>
<DIV></FONT>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I agree that things in the long run will tend towards that direction, so given that, what steps can be implemented to still create a healthy pvp balance?&nbsp; To me, item loot seems the most obvious.&nbsp; People going PvPing would bank their most important PvE gear, and ganking would be rampant for the entire life of the server.&nbsp; </FONT></DIV>
<DIV></FONT>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>The two solutions to the scenario you outlined seem to me to be:</FONT></DIV>
<DIV></FONT>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>1.) Two identical teams - all classes, all races - you choose which side at character creation.&nbsp; The teams are hardcoded so you cannot group, buff, heal, rez, etc opposing teams &amp; there is an enforced maximum population ratio of either 60/40 or 55/45 to ensure a relative population balance so you don't have the problem that SZ had.</FONT></DIV>
<DIV></FONT>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>2.) Make the server Kunark era only, eliminate Velious.&nbsp; Fungis would be about as uber as items get, and you'd be darn sure people would gank each other like crazy to make those change hands (if it was Kunark only, then I'd advocate normal no drop items - I don't recall there being too many pre-Velious)</FONT></DIV>
<DIV></FONT>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Thoughts?</FONT></DIV>	
		</td></tr>
