		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<EM>I am not in favor of item loot either.&nbsp; I&nbsp;believe that&nbsp;powerful guilds would de-gear their less powerful opponents and keep them that way thus furthering the gear imbalance that exists today.&nbsp;&nbsp;Allowing PvP within 20 levels would allow high levels to wear down the intended victim&nbsp;so someone within the&nbsp;item loot range could score the kill and the resulting item loot.</EM>&nbsp; 
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>All this would require is an adjustment of attitude - similar to Discord.&nbsp; People learned very quickly there that you need to work with people you can trust and that you need to be ultra-conservative when levelling.&nbsp; Check the zonelist every 10 seconds, make a friends list with your enemies on it to keep an eye on their movements, etc.&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>With two hardcoded teams (I prefer this method, now that we're talking about it more) would ensure a relative balance - and Velious era gear vs. Kunark era gear is not so overpowering that no one will be able to compete with those who tend to gear up.&nbsp; Not to mention, the whole point would be to attack the raids of your enemies and gank their gear - since you can attack people on uber mobs, jump them when they're fighting an uber mob and score some easy loot!</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>The way to thrive and survive on this server would be through teamwork and through active PvP.&nbsp; That is what PvPers want!</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Could likely steal some UO player marketshare with this server - the goal would be to capture the aggressive and competitive PvP gamers.&nbsp; There are plenty of blue/semi-blue servers that already exist - why not make a REAL red server?</DIV>	
		</td></tr>
