		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV>Hardcoded population-balanced teams is a step in the right direction for sure.&nbsp; My opinion is still that item loot exacerbates the tendency towards bigger concentrations of power (Uber guilds).&nbsp; The&nbsp;resulting top guilds (at least two in this case) would&nbsp;attract most of the players.&nbsp;&nbsp;Those who liked the politics of this would stay and those who did not would go elsewhere.&nbsp; Removing item loot will allow&nbsp;for a greater number of guilds to be viable and more choices for the player.</DIV>	
		</td></tr>
