		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<P>Hmm, within a high end Velious setting, I think that you are right that there would naturally be two large opposing main guilds.&nbsp; However, I think that <EM>with </EM>item loot, it also allows for smaller, more tight knit guilds to flourish, because these organized groups could target and kill members of the uber guilds - and gear themselves up in the process.</P>
<P>As an example, a friend of mine and I (shaman and monk) who were seriously undergeared relative to our competiton used to absolutely dominate people together.&nbsp; In this setting, our playstyle would be encouraged because whenever we killed a target who has a gear advantage, we would make that person weaker, while making ourselves stronger.</P>
<P>Item loot would "dumb down" the level of items used in pvp.&nbsp; People would bank their higher end gear that they didn't want to risk losing when they went out for fights.&nbsp; The great thing about this, is that people who do wear their valuable gear would therefore have advantages in PvP.&nbsp; I think that item loot is absolutely necessary to ensure that the server doesn't turn into a massive PvE fest like the current Zek servers.</P>
<DIV></DIV>	
		</td></tr>
