	<tr>
	
		<td class="msg_user_cell" width="150" valign=top>
		
			 









<a href='/eq/view_profile?user.id=1940'  class="auth_text"  style="font-weight:bold;" >	
<span style='color:#336600;'>Xefin</span></a>
			<br>
			
			<span style="font-size: 8pt;">
			Journeyman<br>
			
				Posts: 76<br>
				
				Registered: 03-02-2004
				
			</span>
			


			
			<br>
			
				<img src="/i/p.gif" height=8 width=150 border=0 alt=""><br>
				
			<a href='/eq/view_profile?user.id=1940'>







</a><br>
			


			
			<p>
			






<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=PVP&message.id=359#M359">24</a> of 127
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 2056 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<P>If the concern is that experience loss isn't harsh enough with rezzes being easy to get, make all PvP deaths unrezzable.&nbsp; Or limit the amount of exp returned on rez.&nbsp; There would be other options as well, time penalties, point loss, etc.&nbsp; At the root I fail to see why item loot is in any way better than a PvP point system with item rewards.&nbsp; It's definitely worse for the guy who loses - he loses a piece of gear that may be critical to him.&nbsp; It's probably worse for the guy who wins - most likely, he gets a piece of gear that he cannot use.&nbsp; </P>
<P>Losing exp is a setback for a character, but unless you lose tons of it, it doesn't make you vastly weaker in PvP or PvE.&nbsp; Losing a key item, on the other hand, could cripple you for future fights.&nbsp; The rich get richer, the poor get poorer - isn't this one of the complaints about current PvP servers?&nbsp; Item loot will not promote balance, because the more gear I have, the easier it is to take your inferior&nbsp;gear.&nbsp; People will not magically stop PvEing on your proposed server.&nbsp; The PvE&nbsp;leaders will&nbsp;just be able to exploit their advantages more easily.&nbsp; Instead of just&nbsp;smacking the undergeared for fun, they can smack them and sell their stuff.</P>
<P>So yeah, I'd suggest the loser loses experience, rez capped at 50%.&nbsp; The winner gets points, and can accumulate points to buy items (a la LDoN).&nbsp; That encourages people to fight and win, without being a system that's punitive and causes people to quit.</P>	
		</td></tr>
		<tr>
		
		<td class="msg_date_cell" valign=bottom nowrap>
		<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
