	<td bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	<td class="subjectbar" height="20" style="font-size: 8pt;padding-left:10px;" width="100%">
		Re: How to Fix EQ PvP - Address the real issue

	</td>
	
		<td class="subjectbar" align=right style="padding:0px;padding-right:10px;">












		<table cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 border=0 id="io_bpvpm360_table" 
		
			onClick="setId('360');showLiMenu(this,'io_bpvpm360','right',false);" 
			onDblClick="setId('360');showLiMenu(this,'io_bpvpm360','right',false);" 
			
		>
		<tr class=clickable>
			
				<td nowrap><a class=subjectbar_text style='font-size: 8pt;'>Options</a></td>
				
			<td>&nbsp;&nbsp;</td>
			<td><img src='/i/skins/default/button_options.gif' border=0 alt='Options' title='Options' width=11 height=28></td>
			<td>&nbsp;</td></tr>
		</table>
		
		</td></tr>
		
	<tr>
	
		<td class="msg_user_cell" width="150" valign=top>
		
			 









<a href='/eq/view_profile?user.id=24860'  class="auth_text"  style="font-weight:bold;" >	
<span style='color:#336600;'>Trynd</span></a>
			<br>
			
			<span style="font-size: 8pt;">
			Journeyman<br>
			
				Posts: 59<br>
				
				Registered: 04-13-2004
				
			</span>
			


			
			<br>
			
				<img src="/i/p.gif" height=8 width=150 border=0 alt=""><br>
				
			<a href='/eq/view_profile?user.id=24860'>







</a><br>
			


			
			<p>
			






<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=PVP&message.id=360#M360">25</a> of 127
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 2054 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV>
<P><EM>If the concern is that experience loss isn't harsh enough with rezzes being easy to get, make all PvP deaths unrezzable.&nbsp; Or limit the amount of exp returned on rez.&nbsp; There would be other options as well, time penalties, point loss, etc.&nbsp; At the root I fail to see why item loot is in any way better than a PvP point system with item rewards.&nbsp; It's definitely worse for the guy who loses - he loses a piece of gear that may be critical to him.&nbsp; It's probably worse for the guy who wins - most likely, he gets a piece of gear that he cannot use.</EM>&nbsp; </P>
<P>If you get a piece of gear you cannot use - give it to your buddy who needs it.&nbsp; The idea behind having the FV item ruleset would be so gear can be distributed.&nbsp; Gear would become necessary to share, and hence this would promote teamwork.</P>
<P><EM>Losing exp is a setback for a character, but unless you lose tons of it, it doesn't make you vastly weaker in PvP or PvE.&nbsp; Losing a key item, on the other hand, could cripple you for future fights.&nbsp; The rich get richer, the poor get poorer - isn't this one of the complaints about current PvP servers?&nbsp; Item loot will not promote balance, because the more gear I have, the easier it is to take your inferior&nbsp;gear.&nbsp; People will not magically stop PvEing on your proposed server.&nbsp; The PvE&nbsp;leaders will&nbsp;just be able to exploit their advantages more easily.&nbsp; Instead of just&nbsp;smacking the undergeared for fun, they can smack them and sell their stuff.</EM></P>
<P>Hence why being able to choose a handful of items that are immune to being looted is a nice fix.&nbsp; People can have their "core" equipment intact, yet lose resist gear, AC, etc if they keep getting killed in PvP.&nbsp; If you keep dying in PvP, find some friends and go gank some other people to get gear back.&nbsp; Gear would change hands constantly.</P>
<P>PvEing pre-Luclin&nbsp;does not give nearly as large of an advantage as it is post-Luclin (PoP in particular).&nbsp; Once you hit lvl 60, the only way to gain power is through items.&nbsp; A level 55 rogue with their epic (for example) is not very different from a level 60 rogue with the same gear - the difference between ATK, HP and AC is marginal at best, and hence the most skilled player will win the fight.</P>
<P>So what is the fear?&nbsp; That a large group of people will PvE effectively to gain "a lead" and then pummel everyone else to keep them down?&nbsp; In the long term this is virtually impossible on an item loot server.&nbsp; By its very nature, item loot will force a re-distribution because those that have the most have the most to lose.&nbsp; Each death of theirs is worth far more (because they'll lose an item that is difficult to replace) than those of the people below them.&nbsp; In this way, an equillibrium will be formed and gear will change hands.</P>
<P>&nbsp;</P>
<P>&nbsp;</P></DIV>	
		</td></tr>
		<tr>
		
		<td class="msg_date_cell" valign=bottom nowrap>
